            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-10-12T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-10-12T03:00:00-05:00" n="1451" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1451">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.953/10–1249: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Tsingtao</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hawthorne</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tsingtao</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-10-12T16:00:00+08:00">October 12, 1949—4 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 11:53 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>560. ConGen’s American staff expect learn action taken on their applications for
                    exit permits October 24. Although ConGen officially closing October 15, will
                    then maintain radio contact until eve actual departure, which will likely be by
                    ship for Hong Kong.</p>
                <p>Department may wish inform NY office Standard Oil [that] George Sevaldson,
                    Norwegian, until recently charge company’s Tsingtao interests, has been trying
                    since August 28 obtain exit permit. No reason given for nonissuance.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hawthorne</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
